Detailed Description

cvmx_gmx::_tx_corrupt

GMX_TX_CORRUPT = TX - Corrupt TX packets with the ERR bit set

Notes: Packets sent from PKO with the ERR wire asserted will be corrupted by the transmitter if CORRUPT[prt] is set (XAUI uses prt==0).

Corruption means that GMX will send a bad FCS value. If GMX_TX_APPEND[FCS] is clear then no FCS is sent and the GMX cannot corrupt it. The corrupt FCS value is 0xeeeeeeee for SGMII/1000Base-X and 4 bytes of the error propagation code in XAUI mode.
